provoke /prəˈvəʊk/

(provoking,provoked,provokes) 

1. V-T If you provoke someone, you deliberately annoy them and try to make them behave aggressively. 对…挑衅 

例： He started beating me when I was about fifteen but I didn't do anything to provoke him. 我大约十五岁时，他开始打我，但我并没有做什么招惹他的事情。 

2. V-T If something provokes a reaction, it causes it. 引起 

例： His election success has provoked a shocked reaction. 他的竞选胜利已经引起了震惊的反应。

